```
if(containerV.hasPropertyEqualTo(GraphPropertyEnum.DISTRIBUTION_STATUS, 
                DistributionStatusEnum.DISTRIBUTION_APPROVED.name(),
                DistributionStatusEnum.DISTRIBUTION_REJECTED.name())) {
  // ...
}
```
This would also prevent a NullPointerException if there is no GraphPropertyEnum.DISTRIBUTION_STATUS is not in the `metadataProperties`
```
public class GraphVertex {
    // ... 
    // if you need this to be more performant at the cost of
    // more cyclomatic complexity, you could desugarized the options with ifs.
    public boolean hasPropertyEqualTo(GraphPropertyEnum metadataProperty, String...values) {
        List<String> vs = Arrays.asList(values);
        return Optional.of(metadataProperties)
            .flatMap(ps -> Optional.of(ps.get(metadataProperty)))
            .map(vs::contains)
            .orElse(false); // We compare an object with a string. This may be a bug
 	}
    // ...
```

